analysis: The documents all pertain to the revocation of previous executive orders that had withdrawn public lands, followed by the opening of these lands for entry under homestead or desert land laws, primarily for ex-service men for a 91-day period, and then to the general public. They all reference Public Resolution 85 of June 12, 1930, which grants service recognition to ex-service men.
title: Revoking Land Withdrawals and Prioritizing Ex-Service Men
